OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Another one bites the dust for New Zealand and Stuart Broad is on fire out there. Broad keeps coming from around the wicket and angles it in from a bit wider of the crease. The ball is pitched up a bit and nips back in off the deck as well. Tom Latham is a bit on the defensive block and the ball just sneaks between bat and pad, going on to hit the top of off stump. Latham cannot believe it and New Zealand have now lost their top 3. Jubilation for Broad though and rightly so.
Commentary.Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: On a hard length and angled into middle, Tom Latham pushes it toward mid on.
Bowls it a tad fuller and angles it into the off pole, Tom Latham makes a solid block.
Good length again around off, Latham blocks this one out.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Zak Crawley puts down a fairly straightforward chance and that's the second one put down by him in this game. Stuart Broad bowls this one on a good length and on a probing line around off. Tom Latham ends up pushing at it with hard hands and gets an outside edge that goes to the left of the second slip. Crawley dives to that side but the ball hits his wrists and goes down to third man. Two taken.
On a good length around the top of off, Tom Latham defends it out.
Full and outside off, Henry Nicholls does not reach out to the delivery and shoulders arms.

Switches to 'round the wicket and lands this one on a good length on off, Henry Nicholls takes a stride forward to defend but gets an inside edge that goes wide of short leg. The ball rolls towards deep backward square leg and batters run two.
Back of a length in the channel outside off, Henry Nicholls carefully lets it go.
Touch on the shorter side at the batter, Henry Nicholls hangs back and pushes it to mid on.
Angled across outside off on a length, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
On a length on off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham pushes this one off the back foot to cover and takes a single.
Ollie Robinson comes into the attack now.
Keeps it on a length at the stumps, Henry Nicholls solidly defends this one back to the bowler.
Henry Nicholls is the new man in.

OUT! BOWLED! Stuart Broad is on a roll here and he now gets Kane Williamson! Bowls this one on a good length on off stump, Kane Williamson presses forward to defend but does not account for the inward movement. The ball beats him on the inside edge and goes through the gap between bat and pad. Sees his woodwork disturbed and he departs for a duck.
Commentary.Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter in length and outside off, Kane Williamson gets on his toes and punches it along the ground to cover.
On a good length around off, swinging into the batter, Kane Williamson gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Kane Williamson gets his bat down and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Pitches this one up on middle and leg, Kane Williamson blocks it toward mid on.
Goes a touch fuller and angles it in sharply from around off, Latham gets his bat down in time.
Slightly pitched up around off and angling in, Tom Latham solidly keeps it out.
Length delivery angling in around off, Tom Latham covers the off stump and leaves the ball alone.
On a length around off, Tom Latham shoulders arms and lets it go.

A polite enquiry but turned down! James Anderson bowls this one back of a length and angling in on middle, Tom Latham gets cramped for room as he looked to work it on the leg side and fails to connect. Ben Foakes behind the wicket thinks he heard something but Ben Stokes is not convinced enough and he opts not to review.
Bowls it full and on off, Tom Latham gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Kane Williamson walks out at number 3.

OUT! TIMBER! This is a peach of a delivery from Stuart Broad! Lands this one on a good length and on off from 'round the wicket, Devon Conway goes for a drive with a straight bat but without any foot movement. The ball jags back in sharply after pitching and crashes into the middle stump. This is a huge wicket for England.
Commentary.Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Full around off by Stuart Broad, Devon Conway gets forward to defend but gets an outside edge that rolls to the slip cordon.
Keeps it full around off, Tom Latham presses forward and taps it to cover for a quick single.
Goes full this time on off, Tom Latham defends this one off the front foot.
Full and angling down the leg side, Tom Latham goes for the clip but misses.
Back of a length on off from 'round the wicket, Tom Latham stays on the back foot and steers this one past gully for a couple of runs.
Fullish length and on middle and leg, this is clipped away leg side for a single.
Full again and around off by James Anderson, Tom Latham presses forward and defends this one on the off side.
Goes fuller on off, Tom Latham gets on the front foot and pushes this one towards cover.
On a good length on middle by James Anderson, Tom Latham defends this one down the wicket.
Full and tailing in on off, Devon Conway shuffles across and clips this one off his front pad towards mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls this one back of a length on off and shapes back in, Devon Conway looks to defend this one in front but gets an inside edge onto his front pad.
Slight halt! Tom Latham has a bit of an issue with the gloves and the 12th man comes onto the ground with a new pair. All good to go.
Nails the inswinging yorker on middle, Tom Latham gets his bat down in time and digs this one out to cover.
Full and on off, Tom Latham gets on the front foot and defends it on the off side.
Full and around off by Stuart Broad, Devon Conway gets across and works it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Full again and slightly on leg, Tom Latham flicks this one through square leg. The ball does not have legs on it to reach the fence and the batters run three.
FOUR! Full and angling into the pads, Tom Latham lets the ball come to him and clips it through mid-wicket for the first boundary of New Zealand's chase.
Starts with a good-length delivery outside off, Tom Latham takes a stride forward and leaves the ball alone.
Stuart Broad to bowl from the other end.
Lands this one full and swinging away outside off, Devon Conway shoulders arms once again.
Length delivery outside off, Devon Conway is in no mood to play at those and lets it go.
Full and on off by James Anderson, Devon Conway confidently gets behind the line and defends it on the off side.
On a length and around off from 'round the wicket, the ball jags back in after pitching, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Touch fuller and outside off, going away from the batter, Devon Conway shoulders arms and lets it go.
Tom Latham and New Zealand are underway in the chase! James Anderson starts with a back-of-a-length delivery, swinging away outside off, Tom Latham taps it to point and sets off for a quick single.
